Carbonade Flamande

1kg Beef
300g Smoked Bacon
2 Onions, sliced thinly
1 Sprig Thyme
2 Bay Leaves
50g Flour
60g Butter
50g Light Brown Sugar
1 Bottle Beer
2 Slices Country Bread
50g Brown Mustard

Fry bacon in a dutch oven until crispy.
Remove, add butter, and sauté sliced onion until brown.
Remove, add butter and beef, and brown on all sides.
Add flour, and mix to coat.
Add onions and bacon back in along with thyme and bay, salt and pepper.
Add light brown sugar, stir till caramelized, then deglaze with beer.
Place 2 slices of country bread spread with mustard on top of the stew.
Cover and stew for 2h30.


MISE

Show Thyme
Show Bay
Show Brown Sugar
Open Beer
Slice Onions
Cut Potatoes
Place Potatoes in Water
Dice Bacon
Cube Beef

COOK
Fry Bacon
Remove
Add Butter
Sauté Onions
Remove
Add Butter
Brown Beef
Add Onions & Bacon
Add Flour and mix to coat
Add Thyme & Bay
Add Salt & Pepper
Add Sugar & mix
Add Beer
Spread Mustard on Bread
Add Bread
Cover
Stew for 2h30

Make fries
Dry Potatoes
Fry for 6 minutes at 275° F
Rest for 10 minutes
Fry for 1.5 to 3 minutes at 330° F

Serve